<%# HOVERING CONTENT %>
  <div id="introduction" class="single__wrapper">
    <div class="single__content">
      <a href="#introduction" class="guide__suggestion guide__suggestion__padding">
        <div class="guide__suggestion__number guide__suggestion__number--bottom">1.</div>
      </a>

      <h2 class="single__sub__header">Introduction</h2>
      <p>Hovering is a meditation technique that I created to assist people new to meditation. It significantly helps those who struggle to meditate via traditional means.</p>
      <p>It's easy to understand, simple to practice and accessible to people of all ages.</p>
      <p>Unlike traditional meditation, Hovering aims to be highly concrete as opposed to highly abstract, so you can have that 'ah-ha' moment of clarity a lot sooner rather than later.</p>
      <p>Essentially how it works is that you hover your cursor over the hover button and you use this as a tool to help ground your mind.</p>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; margin-top: 3.6rem; margin-bottom: 3.6rem;">
        <div class="circle__container cr">
          <div id="hoverCircleExampleHover" class="circle cri">
            <div id="hoverCircleTextHover" class="circle__text">
              Hover
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <script>
        const hoverCircleExampleHover = document.querySelector('#hoverCircleExampleHover');
        const hoverCircleTextHover = document.querySelector('#hoverCircleTextHover');

        hoverCircleExampleHover.onmouseenter = function() {
          hoverCircleTextHover.classList.add("hover__text__fade");
          document.body.classList.add("main__dark");
        }
        hoverCircleExampleHover.onmouseleave = function() {
          hoverCircleTextHover.classList.remove("hover__text__fade");
          document.body.classList.remove("main__dark");
        }
      </script>

      <p>Of course, that's just the basics of it.</p>
      <p>It's actually quite a lot more involved. For example, it's important that you keep your hand attached to your cursor while you practice Hovering.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

